{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"0ab9f9c0-b46a-41c3-8895-ec3637c26ff6","content":"Yes, you'll hit compatibility issues. MSTest v3 (the `MSTest` meta-package or `3.x` versions of the individual packages) **dropped support** for several older TFMs, including:\n\n- **`net462`** — .NET Framework < 4.6.2 is unsupported, but `net462` itself is the minimum supported .NET Framework version, so it *should* still work.\n- **`netcoreapp3.1`** — ❌ **Dropped.** MSTest v3 requires at least `net6.0` for .NET Core/.NET targets.\n- **`net5.0`** — ❌ **Dropped.** Also out of support; MSTest v3 requires `net6.0`+.\n\n### What you need to do\n\n1. **Update your target frameworks.** Replace the EOL TFMs:\n   - `net5.0` → `net6.0` (or newer)\n   - `netcoreapp3.1` → `net6.0` (or newer)\n   - `net462` can stay (it's the minimum supported .NET Framework).\n\n2. **Switch to the unified `MSTest` package** (recommended for v3):\n   ```xml\n   <PackageReference Include=\"MSTest\" Version=\"3.x.x\" />\n   ```\n   This replaces both `MSTest.TestFramework` and `MSTest.TestAdapter`.\n\n3. **Review breaking API changes** — some attributes and assert APIs were renamed or removed in v3. Check the [MSTest v3 migration guide](https://learn.microsoft.com/dotnet/core/testing/mstest-sdk-overview) for details.\n\n**TL;DR:** Two of your three TFMs (`net5.0`, `netcoreapp3.1`) are incompatible with MSTest v3. Update them to `net6.0`+ before migrating.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"441ea3d0-1763-4668-a154-7197de84f6d7","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user's project targets `net5.0`, `net462`, and `netcoreapp3.1`. MSTest v3 has dropped support for some older frameworks. Let me provide guidance.","outputTokens":508,"requestId":"A030:3C520:104C487:1332A14:69FE9FFC"},"id":"ba9fd04f-02d9-47b4-a4ad-c42cf716ef22","timestamp":"2026-05-09T02:46:31.395Z","parentId":"2fe8a63b-b79c-4727-9854-860402aa1c1a"}
